### Content Sources (Phase 2)

#### [NEW] [pipeline/sources/reddit_scraper.py](file:///c:/Users/Admin/OneDrive/Desktop/content_automation_pipeline/pipeline/sources/reddit_scraper.py)
- Uses PRAW to fetch top 10 hot posts from each configured subreddit
- Extracts: title, score, url, subreddit, comment_count, created_utc
- Deduplicates by URL and filters posts older than 24 hours
- Returns standardized `TrendingTopic` dataclass list

#### [NEW] [pipeline/sources/rss_fetcher.py](file:///c:/Users/Admin/OneDrive/Desktop/content_automation_pipeline/pipeline/sources/rss_fetcher.py)
- Uses `feedparser` to parse all configured RSS feed URLs
- Extracts: title, summary, link, published date
- Filters to last 24 hours only
- Returns same `TrendingTopic` dataclass format

---

### AI Content Generation (Phase 3)

#### [NEW] [pipeline/content/topic_selector.py](file:///c:/Users/Admin/OneDrive/Desktop/content_automation_pipeline/pipeline/content/topic_selector.py)
- Takes all trending topics from sources
- Sends to Gemini API with prompt: "Rank these by virality potential for a tech audience. Pick the top 4: 1 for a video, 3 for text posts. Avoid duplicates."
- Returns `SelectedTopics` with `video_topic` and `text_topics`

#### [NEW] [pipeline/content/text_generator.py](file:///c:/Users/Admin/OneDrive/Desktop/content_automation_pipeline/pipeline/content/text_generator.py)
- Takes a topic, generates platform-optimized text
- X post: 280 chars max, punchy, with hashtags
- LinkedIn post: 1300 chars, professional but casual, with hook + insight + CTA
- Uses Gemini API with tone prompt: casual + educational

#### [NEW] [pipeline/content/image_fetcher.py](file:///c:/Users/Admin/OneDrive/Desktop/content_automation_pipeline/pipeline/content/image_fetcher.py)
- Takes topic keywords, searches Pexels Photos API
- Downloads best matching landscape image
- Resizes/optimizes for each platform

#### [NEW] [pipeline/content/video_generator.py](file:///c:/Users/Admin/OneDrive/Desktop/content_automation_pipeline/pipeline/content/video_generator.py)
- **Script**: Gemini generates a 30-60 second narration script with hook + body + conclusion
- **TTS**: `edge-tts` converts script to `.mp3` with `en-US-GuyNeural` voice
- **Footage**: Pexels Video API fetches 3-5 relevant clips based on topic keywords
- **Compose**: MoviePy stitches clips, overlays TTS audio, adds animated word-by-word captions
- **Output**: 1080x1920 (9:16) MP4 video, ≤60 seconds

